"*1533159*\r\n15-33159 (E)\r\nThis record contains the text of speeches delivered in English and of the translation of speeches \r\ndelivered in other languages. Corrections should be submitted to the original languages only. \r\nThey should be incorporated in a copy of the record and sent under the signature of a member \r\nof the delegation concerned to the Chief of the Verbatim Reporting Service, room U-0506 \r\n(verbatimrecords@un.org). Corrected records will be reissued electronically on the Official \r\nDocument System of the United Nations (http://documents.un.org).\r\nThe meeting was called to order at 3.05 p.m.\r\nAgenda item 122 (continued)\r\nStrengthening of the United Nations system\r\nDraft resolution (A/70/L.4)\r\nThe President: Members will recall that the \r\nAssembly considered agenda item 122 at its 29th \r\nand 30th plenary meetings, held on 12 October. I \r\nwish to thank all delegations for their proposals and \r\ncooperation, which resulted in the submission of the \r\ndraft resolution under this item. I particularly thank \r\nthe Spanish delegation for undertaking the process of \r\nconsultations. It is fitting that the General Assembly \r\nshould consider a declaration on the occasion of the \r\nseventieth anniversary of our Organization, in which \r\nwe solemnly reaffirm our faith in the United Nations \r\nand our unfailing commitment to the purposes and \r\nprinciples of the Charter, as well as to the Charter in its \r\nentirety, and on the eve of the anniversary of its entry \r\ninto force.\r\nThe Assembly will now take a decision on draft \r\nresolution A/70/L.4, entitled “Declaration on the \r\noccasion of the seventieth anniversary of the United \r\nNations”. May I take it that the Assembly decides to \r\nadopt it?\r\nDraft resolution A/70/L.4 was adopted (resolution \r\n70/3).\r\nThe President: The Assembly has thus concluded \r\nthis stage of its consideration of agenda item 122.\r\nThe meeting rose at 3.10 p.m.\r\nUnited Nations A/70/PV.38\r\nGeneral Assembly\r\nSeventieth session\r\n38th plenary meeting\r\nFriday, 23 October 2015, 3 p.m. \r\nNew York\r\nOfficial Records\r\nPresident: Mr. Lykketoft . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .  (Denmark)\r\n"